One real-world application that can be built using Salesforce is a Hospital Management System.
In this application, Salesforce can be used to manage:
patient records,
doctor appointments,
billing details,
medical history,
customer support services.
For example, when a patient books an appointment, the system can automatically store their details, schedule the appointment with a doctor, send reminder messages, and maintain the patient’s medical records in one place. Hospital staff can quickly access patient information, which helps improve service and reduce paperwork.
Salesforce can also generate reports about patient visits, doctor performance, and hospital operations, helping management make better decisions.
In simple words, Salesforce helps build smart business applications that automate processes, organize data, and improve customer or patient experience.
